	<p>I get a kick out of the right's constant refrain that we need to cut government, while it is their administrations that keep growing government.  The budget went through the roof under Reagan, Bush the First and Bush the Second, while it shrank under Clinton.  If you wish to decrease government spending, elect a Democrat.<br />
<br />
I also love how the right is always down on Personal Welfare, but never says a thing about Corporate Welfare.  &quot;Screw helping individuals, but profitable mega-corporations need our help.&quot;  What a bizarre and unGodly view of things.<br />
<br />
And a flat tax is not equitable.  I don't believe it to be fair to take the same percentage of money from the poor as you take from the wealthy.  The poor need every dollar they can get their hands upon in order to stay off the streets and off welfare.  And changing the system now after how dependent society has become regarding various tax breaks and incentives, would be devastating to many aspects of the economy.  And I believe that limited, personal tax incentives are a useful spur to economic growth</p>
	
	
	
